articles.title: Argentina's cabinet chief says harvest should bring economic relief
articles.description: Argentina's financial crisis, which has been marked by exchange rate volatility and soaring inflation, should start abating in November and December, with large foreign currency inflows from the wheat harvest, cabinet chief Agustin Rossi told Reuters on Friday.

articles.description: The lewd-looking 10-inch worms landed on the shore after being uprooted in a storm.
